headline: Dell misses Q3 revenue estimates, now the stock is sliding
summary: Dell Technologies (DELL) shares take a tumble in Tuesday's extended hours after the computer and software manufacturer posted its third quarter results, missing on revenue ($24.37 billion vs. consensus estimates of $24.59 billion) but topping earnings estimates (adjusted earnings of $2.15 per share vs. consensus estimates of $2.05 per share). Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton review Dell's Q3 earnings performance, eyeing revenue in particular business segments such as Dell's server, networking, and infrastructure solutions group (ISG) units. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Dell's third-quarter revenue misses on PC weakness
summary: Dell reported revenue of $24.37 billion in the quarter, compared with the average analyst estimate of $24.67 billion, according to data compiled by LSEG.  Despite booming demand for Dell's AI-optimized servers used to handle large AI workloads, its traditional PC segment has been facing stiff competition from rivals such as HP and weaker consumer spending amid an uncertain economy.  Revenue from Dell's client solutions group, which houses its PC business, came in at $12.13 billion, below expectations of $12.43 billion.

headline: Dell Technologies Delivers Third Quarter Fiscal 2025 Financial Results
summary: Full storyDell Technologies (NYSE: DELL) announces financial results for its fiscal 2025 third quarter. Revenue was $24.4 billion, up 10% year over year. Operating income was $1.7 billion and non-GAAP operating income was $2.2 billion, both up 12% year over year. Diluted earnings per share was $1.58, and non-GAAP diluted earnings per share was $2.15, up 16% and 14% year over year, respectively.
